ABUJA (SundiataPost) – Nigeria on Saturday moved towards hitting the 20,000 mark in COVID-19 infections.According to the latest update of the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) released on Saturday night, 661 new cases of the pandemic were recorded, bringing the total number of confirmed cases in Nigeria to 19,808.Also the number of those whose lives have been claimed by the pandemic has climbed to 506. It was 487 as at Friday.The full report is as follows: 661 new cases of #COVID19Nigeria; Lagos-230Rivers-127Delta-83FCT-60Oyo-51Edo-31Bayelsa-27Kaduna-25Plateau-13Ondo-6Nasarawa-3Ekiti-2Kano-2Borno-1 19,808 confirmed6,718 discharged506 deaths See the state by state breakdown below: ABUJA - Deaths resulting from the COVID-19 pandemic in Nigeria has increased to 128 according to information made available by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on Saturday night. On a positive note, the number of discharged patients increased to 745. In the same vein the NCDC announced the… May 10, 2020 In "Top Stories" ABUJA - Lagos, the epicentre of coronavirus in Nigeria and the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) on Saturday got observers worried as both cities recorded new infections in huge numbers.According to the report by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC), there were 220 new cases out of which Lagos and… May 3, 2020 In "Top Stories" ABUJA - The COVID-19 situation in Kano State took a dangerous dimension on Friday as the state for the second day topped Lagos, the epicentre of the pandemic in Nigeria. Out of the 238 new cases announced by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC), Kano recorded 92 new cases… May 1, 2020 In "Top Stories"